<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><!DOCTYPE legaldoc PUBLIC "Nebraska Unicameral//DTD legaldoc XML v1.0//EN" "legaldoc.dtd"><legaldoc><law type="statute"><section><sectno></sectno><amendatorysection chaptername="Banks and Banking" statutenumber="8-1,120"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>8-1,120</statuteno><catchline>Violators; apprehension and conviction; rewards.</catchline><para>The department may offer and pay out of the funds appropriated to it rewards for the apprehension and conviction of any person or persons violating the Nebraska Banking Act, but such rewards shall not exceed two hundred fifty dollars in any one case.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1909, c. 10, &#167; 60, p. 95; </para><para>R.S.1913, &#167; 340; </para><para>Laws 1919, c. 190, tit. V, art. XVI, &#167; 60, p. 710; </para><para>C.S.1922, &#167; 8040; </para><para>C.S.1929, &#167; 8-1,103; </para><para>Laws 1933, c. 18, &#167; 70, p. 170; </para><para>C.S.Supp.,1941, &#167; 8-1,103; </para><para>R.S.1943, &#167; 8-1,108; </para><para>Laws 1963, c. 29, &#167; 120, p. 184; </para><para>Laws 1987, LB 2, &#167; 20; </para><para>Laws 1998, LB 1321, &#167; 26.</para></source></law></legaldoc>